collectionDetail.name: The Only Bun for Me
collectionDetail.introduction: Find the best burger to your fries!

experiences.introduction: Craving for some quality burger made with premium and juicy Angus beef patties? Expect nothing less from Moo Moo Plus’ array of sumptuous handmade burgers. Try their grilled chicken burgers, too!
experiences.name: Moo Moo Plus

experiences.introduction: A top choice for after-work drinks, where an effortlessly chic ambience meets classic American mixology. Our favourite drinks include the English House Punch and the Tarling!
experiences.name: The Diplomat

experiences.introduction: Honbo’s soft-shell crab burger is a delicacy that comes with Old Bay Tatar sauce and ginger coleslaw. First timers will love the resto’s potato milk buns developed with its artisanal baker.
experiences.name: Honbo

experiences.introduction: With rich Black Angus beef patty, American cheddar, and Butcher’s Shop bacon, Henry’s signature burger will leave meat-lovers munching until the last crumb.
experiences.name: Henry

experiences.introduction: A rich and flavourful bacon cheeseburger? Grab it from Beef & Liberty Burgers! It is topped with New Zealand bacon, carameralised onions, and creamy raclette.
experiences.name: Beef & Liberty Burgers - Sheung Wan

experiences.introduction: A rich and flavourful bacon cheeseburger? Grab it from Beef & Liberty Burgers! It is topped with New Zealand bacon, carameralised onions, and creamy raclette.
experiences.name: Beef & Liberty Burgers - Stanley

experiences.introduction: Electric Ave’s sumptuous Black Daddy beef burger is topped with English black pudding and house-made pickles. Other burgers in the restaurant’s menu are also worth a try!
experiences.name: Smashed by Electric Ave

experiences.introduction: The Big Bite’s Canadian sirloin patties are grilled in an open flame to bring out that juicy goodness that any burger-lover will enjoy. Want something new? Try its unique Peanut Butter and Jam Burger.
experiences.name: The Big Bite

experiences.introduction: Burger Circus is where burger-lovers can enjoy classic American dining vibes with its 5-ounce USDA-certified prime burger patties. These are freshly ground and grilled to order any time of the day.
experiences.name: Burger Circus

experiences.introduction: Recommended by the Michelin Guide, The Butchers Club uses Australian dry-aged Angus beef patties for its burgers. It even offers a neat selection of classic vegan and vegetarian burgers.
experiences.name: The Butchers Club - Wan Chai

experiences.introduction: Recommended by the Michelin Guide, The Butchers Club uses Australian dry-aged Angus beef patties for its burgers. It even offers a neat selection of classic vegan and vegetarian burgers.
experiences.name: The Butchers Club - Quarry Bay

experiences.introduction: Morty’s Smoked Meat Burger is a real treat with Australian Angus beef patty, tomato, cheddar, pickles, lettuce, and Thousand Island dressing. Its bread, sauces, dressings, and more are handmade.
experiences.name: Morty's

experiences.introduction: Quarter Master’s Blue Cheese Burger is a crowd favourite and comes with bacon jam, cashel blue cheese, and rocket leaves. Just the right juiciness, taste, and size.
experiences.name: Quarter Master

collectionDetail.name: Healthy Eats
collectionDetail.introduction: Good health is at the root of it all

experiences.name: Mana! Slow Fast Food - Wan Chai

collectionDetail.name: Date Night
collectionDetail.introduction: We highly rate these spots for a date.

experiences.introduction: Man Wah’s not-so-extensive menu is a mark of this fine dining restaurant’s focus and innovation to its dishes. Wagyu beef puffs dim sum seasoned with black pepper sauce is a must-try!
experiences.name: Man Wah

experiences.introduction: Spice up your date night by trying Lebanese cuisine at Sumac. Named after a popular spice used in the Arabic world, this restaurant offers al fresco dining for a more romantic atmosphere.
experiences.name: Sumac

experiences.introduction: Looking for delicious Japanese cuisine to go with fine cocktails? Go to The Aubrey for an eccentric Japanese izakaya dining experience. Its 25th-floor location gives nice views of Victoria Harbour.
experiences.name: The Aubrey

experiences.introduction: A beautiful, romantic setting and good food on a date night? Get them both from Dear Lilly! This place is love inspired all around, from bouquets, trinkets, love letters, romantic quotes, and more.
experiences.name: Dear Lilly

experiences.introduction: Fancying a Parisian ambience with a view of the harbour? Head on to The French Window, a brasserie offering a French menu with a twist. Try their six-course degustation menu with wine pairing.
experiences.name: The French Window

experiences.introduction: From ornate chandeliers to mirrors and more, Hugo’s got that classic European style ambience to set a romantic mood with your date. Don’t miss out on the restaurant’s world-class steak dishes.
experiences.name: Hugo's

experiences.introduction: Immersing in the classy European-themed interiors of Junon on a date night is as romantic as it gets. This revolving restaurant will give you a stunning 360-degree view of the harbour.
experiences.name: Junon

experiences.introduction: Enjoy a romantic dinner at Madame Fù with free-flowing sparkling, white, and red wines while munching on sumptuous Chinese dishes. Free Flow All Day starts after 6:00 PM, Monday to Thursday.
experiences.name: Madame Fu

experiences.introduction: An intimate dinner night awaits you at The Veranda. Popular as a wedding venue, this restaurant specialises in serving traditional Continental dishes with a modern twist.
experiences.name: The Verandah

experiences.introduction: A discreet, romantic setting where you can bring your own alcohol? Look no further than Le Blanc, a French restaurant featuring private compartments for you and your date to have more privacy.
experiences.name: Le Blanc

experiences.introduction: Indulge in the rich-tasting Thai cuisine served at Sip Song. This casual beachside eatery and bar is where you and our date can enjoy sumptuous steamed mullet fish and roti pancakes with BBQ pork.
experiences.name: Sip Song

experiences.introduction: If you’re looking for authentic Japanese cuisine with your date, bring him or her to Sagano. For a more immersive dining and cultural experience, try the restaurant’s tatami VIP room.
experiences.name: Sagano

collectionDetail.name: Fine Dining
collectionDetail.introduction: Indulge with the masters of haute cuisine

experiences.introduction: Duddell’s is known for making aesthetically pleasing dim sum dishes. Try its garoupa dumplings with spicy termite mushroom and shrimp arranged as a “fish pond” that’s too beautiful to eat.
experiences.name: Duddell’s

experiences.introduction: Man Wah’s not-so-extensive menu is a mark of this fine dining restaurant’s focus and innovation to its dishes. Wagyu beef puffs dim sum seasoned with black pepper sauce is a must-try!
experiences.name: Man Wah

experiences.introduction: From ornate chandeliers to mirrors and more, Hugo’s got that classic European style ambience to set a romantic mood with your date. Don’t miss out on the restaurant’s world-class steak dishes.
experiences.name: Hugo's

experiences.introduction: An intimate dinner night awaits you at The Veranda. Popular as a wedding venue, this restaurant specialises in serving traditional Continental dishes with a modern twist.
experiences.name: The Verandah

experiences.introduction: While Spring Moon’s dumplings are already sumptuous on their own, try these with its signature XO sauce for an added flavour. Minced pork and Sicilian red prawn dim sum are crowd favourites.
experiences.name: Spring Moon

experiences.introduction: Man Ho prides itself on serving homemade dim sum. This acclaimed eatery offers steamed, pan-fried, baked, and deep-fried dim sum, so you have a lot of choices for your upcoming gathering.
experiences.name: Man Ho

experiences.introduction: Fancy a dim sum fix with a view of Victoria Harbour? Head on to Lung King Heen and have a taste of steamed scallop and lobster dumpling as well as the Racan pigeon dim sum with taro, to name a few.
experiences.name: Lung King Heen

experiences.introduction: Sheraton’s Celestial Court adds modern spins to classic dim sum through its famed har gow dish, which you can enjoy with Chinese tea. The restaurant’s signature shrimp dumplings are also worth a try.
experiences.name: Celestial Court

collectionDetail.name: Dim Sum Legends
collectionDetail.introduction: You win sum, you dim sum!

experiences.name: Mott 32

experiences.introduction: Lin Heung Tea is where you can get classic dim sum while appreciating what Hong Kong used to be. It’s an old-school trolly service so be sure to catch on to the servers before the dishes run out!
experiences.name: Lin Heung Tea

experiences.name: Celestial Court

experiences.introduction: Seventh Son is known for its iconic dim sums such as steamed char siu buns and pork dumplings. If you want something sweet, try the upscale eatery’s glutinous dumpling with red bean paste
experiences.name: Seventh Son

experiences.introduction: Kin’s Kitchen sumptuous steamed dishes include meat and shrimp dumpling with truffle paste topping. Its sweet treats such as the water chestnut pudding and sesame rolls are worth a try.
experiences.name: Kin's Kitchen

collectionDetail.introduction: The knead-to-know pizza spots in town!

experiences.introduction: Free-flow beer, wings and fries for $108. This is definitely one of the craziest deals we've seen in Soho. Weekdays from 5pm-7pm.
